{"type": "article", "id": 5878, "title": "在《纽约客》上看雪", "description": "Best On The Web 是一个推荐性栏目，每个工作日我们会从互联网世界中找出最好看的内容，希望这个栏目让我们始终与阅读、知识和美好在一起。", "date": "2015-02-04T08:03:06Z", "super_tag": null, "tags": [{"id": 117, "name": "纽约"}, {"id": 6587, "name": "暴风雪"}, {"id": 1384, "name": "纽约客"}, {"id": 2598, "name": "中央公园"}], "category": 12, "author": 13, "comment_count": 0, "praise_count": 21, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160604223410ZTkBuK4lazCbY85V.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<strong>New Yorker</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<strong><a href=\"http://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/cover-story-2015-02-09?utm_source=tny&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=dailyemail&amp;mbid=nl_020215_Daily&amp;CNDID=27075598&amp;spMailingID=7470134&amp;spUserID=NzkzNjY1NzkwODUS1&amp;spJobID=620190617&amp;spReportId=NjIwMTkwNjE3S0\" target=\"_blank\">Cover Story: Mark Ulriksen's  “A Walk in the Snow</a></strong><strong><a href=\"http://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/cover-story-2015-02-09?utm_source=tny&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=dailyemail&amp;mbid=nl_020215_Daily&amp;CNDID=27075598&amp;spMailingID=7470134&amp;spUserID=NzkzNjY1NzkwODUS1&amp;spJobID=620190617&amp;spReportId=NjIwMTkwNjE3S0\" target=\"_blank\">”</a> </strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t每年出现一个关于雪的封面，已经成了《纽约客》这本杂志的固定项目。今年也不例外，最新一期封面上出现了大雪之后，很多人带着狗到中央公园玩耍的情景，而且都是典型的纽约冬日的一袭黑衣。\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223406IayWuBNSOQ4mvYdk.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.3703125\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t选择用狗作为主角之一，是因为 Unriksen 最近完成了一本名为<strong><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Dogs-Rule-Nonchalantly-Mark-Ulriksen/dp/1939621100\" target=\"_blank\"> Dogs Rule Nonchalantly 的书</a></strong>，里边讲到了自己为什么偏爱画狗——「它们观察你的每个动作，琢磨你的情绪变化，认真地听你讲的每一句话——直到听到你把薯片袋子打开的飒飒声，在暴风雪的时候，它意味着等着你把门打开」。下面是一些 Unriksen 书中画的狗。\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223406kKjNQaStFo3CZcIB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.2703125\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223407dmWFCjbEyhN43utB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.99375\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t下面是过去《纽约客》以雪为主题的一些封面。\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/201606042234079C70KtExscIa1AgZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.3625\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t以色列艺术家 Hanuka 完成的《完美的暴风雪》（Perfect Storm）\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223408Fa7ZsqcbR1AY6nBU.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.359375\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223408X0QbFewgIrBdEl3t.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.3671875\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223409Lisg0wFvIyq8fljB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.3328125\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223409QO0sSI43CGBk1dg5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.35625\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604223410HrUSkYV8Cyl0fLDQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.3921875\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\n\n\n"}